## Maven Command to run Spring Boot Service Instance with parsing arguments for the instance ID. {ja3}

mvn spring-boot:run -Dspring-boot.run.arguments=--spring.application.instance_id=ja3

## Run with arguments and Defined Server Port : 

mvn spring-boot:run -Dspring-boot.run.arguments=--spring.application.instance_id=ja3_2,--server.port=8999


Commands : 

Run Eureka Service "Photo App Discovery Service"
Run API Gateway
Run Instances of Microservices Registered As Eureka Clients.
Load Balancer "Spring Cloud" will ensure routing requests between the diffrence instances " Load Balancing".